## 5. KITTY

### Overview
A GPU-accelerated, feature-rich terminal emphasizing performance, keyboard-centric workflow, and graphical capabilities.

### Performance
- **GPU Rendering**: Yes (OpenGL with threaded rendering)
- **CPU Usage**: 6-8% (excellent)
- **Startup Time**: Very fast
- **Scrolling**: Exceptionally smooth, excellent frame consistency
- **Rendering**: Uses SIMD vector CPU instructions for optimal performance
- **Performance Tradeoffs**: Configurable to tune responsiveness vs efficiency

### Key Features
- **GPU-Accelerated Rendering**: SIMD-optimized with threading
- **Graphics Protocol**: Kitty Image Protocol for inline image display
- **Font Support**: Ligatures, emoji handling with proper spacing, combining accents
- **True Color**: Full 24-bit color support
- **Tabs & Windows**: Multiple layouts with keyboard-centric navigation
- **Kittens**: Plugin ecosystem for extending functionality
- **Copy/Paste**: Multiple buffers like Vim
- **Keyboard-Centric**: Designed for power users
- **Configuration**: Single config file, simple format
- **Scrollback**: Efficient with timestamp support
- **Cross-platform**: Linux, macOS, some BSD distributions

### Technical Details
- **Language**: Python (frontend) + C (rendering engine)
- **Rendering**: OpenGL with GPU acceleration
- **Architecture**: Clean separation of concerns

### Limitations
- **Learning Curve**: Keyboard shortcuts can be complex
- **macOS Status**: Good but Linux-first development
- **Plugin Ecosystem**: Smaller than iTerm2 or Hyper
- **Complex Features**: Advanced features have steep learning curve

### Use Cases
- Linux terminal enthusiasts
- Developers needing inline graphics
- Keyboard-centric workflow users
- Systems administrators
- Performance-sensitive applications (rendering graphs, images)

### Community
- Active development
- Strong documentation
- Growing ecosystem
- Popular among Linux professionals

### Advanced Features
- Hyperlink support
- Customizable colors and themes
- Advanced key binding strategies
- Window tiling and layout management

