## 11. ZOC

### Overview
A professional, commercial terminal emulator and SSH client for Windows and macOS, established since 1993, known for comprehensive features and robust engineering.

### Performance
- **CPU Usage**: Efficient
- **Rendering**: Fast, native code
- **Startup**: Quick
- **Platforms**: Windows 10/11, macOS Sequoia

### Key Features
- **Extensive Terminal Emulations**:
  - VT52, VT100, VT102, VT220, VT420/VT520 (full implementation)
  - Tested with vttest suite (105 points - excellent)
  - ANSI-BBS, ANSI-SCO, Avatar
  - Sun-CDE, Wyse WY-30/50/60
  - TVI 9xx series, QNX, HP, ATT, SNI
  - TTY and many proprietary terminals
- **SSH/Security**:
  - Modern Secure Shell (based on OpenSSH v9.1)
  - Public/private key authentication
  - Smart-card support (PKCS#11, CAC/PIV)
  - Port forwarding and tunneling
  - FIDO2 hardware tokens and Yubikey support
  - SSH Agent forwarding
  - Dynamic port forwarding (SOCKS proxy)
  - X11 forwarding
- **Communication Protocols**:
  - Telnet (RFC-Telnet, SSL-Telnet with TLS 1.2/1.3)
  - Rlogin
  - Modem via serial port and TAPI
  - Direct serial console via USB/serial adapters
  - ISDN with X.25/X.31 support
  - IPv6 support
- **Advanced Features**:
  - Tabbed sessions with thumbnail overview
  - Session thumbnails showing live preview
  - Colorful tabs (tint UI by host)
  - Full keyboard remapping
  - Host directory with folders
  - User-defined button bar with macros
  - F-Macro keys
  - Local typing with history
- **File Transfer**:
  - SCP, FTP, SFTP, FTPS
  - X/Y/Z-modem, Kermit
  - Character translation
  - IND$FILE (IBM mainframes)
- **Automation & Scripting**:
  - REXX language support (75+ extensions)
  - AutoLogin sequences
  - Auto Macros (trigger on sending text)
  - Auto Replies (trigger on receiving text)
  - DDE support (Windows)
  - AppleScript support (macOS)
- **Logging & Monitoring**:
  - Scrollback (3 variants)
  - Auto Highlight of text patterns
  - Raw data trace (text/binary)
  - Hex debug mode
  - File-log with timestamps
  - Printer output

### Technical Details
- **License**: Commercial ($80 USD)
- **Free Trial**: 30-day evaluation
- **Language**: Professional native code
- **Architecture**: Robust, proven design

### Limitations
- **Cost**: $80 commercial license required
- **Closed Source**: Not open-source
- **Platform Limited**: Windows and macOS only (no Linux)
- **User Base**: Smaller than open-source alternatives
- **UI Styling**: Somewhat dated appearance

### Advanced Capabilities
- **Terminal Emulation Depth**: Unmatched legacy support (mainframes, terminals from 1970s-1980s)
- **Scripting Power**: REXX language with 75+ extensions
- **Character Accuracy**: Industry-standard vttest suite validation
- **Hardware Support**: Smart cards, tokens, serial devices

### Use Cases
- Enterprise IT departments
- Legacy system administrators
- Mainframe operators (TN3270/TN5250)
- Professional users needing certainty
- Network engineers with diverse equipment
- Organizations with legacy infrastructure

### Philosophy
- "Swiss Army Knife of terminal emulators"
- Versatile, robust, proven engineering
- Professional-grade reliability

### Community
- Established user base
- Professional support
- Enterprise adoption
- Solo developer support (excellent responsiveness)

